{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Jira reconciler correctness & the ticket-store corruption it caused\n\nBroadened from the original store-only charter (f193 follow-ups). Root-cause work (bug\nsaggy-pupil-plant / f193 and the 2026-07-07 reconciler deep-dive, session log\nspirited-balsamic-sealion) established the throughline: **the Jira reconciler is the epicenter**.\nIts 20-min CI pass is the busiest concurrent writer of the `tickets` branch, and its shallow-fetch +\nrebase workflow (RC1) *caused* the ~2,400-issue store corruption. Four bands:\n(A) store hardening + remediation, (B) convergence completion, (C) latent-gap closure,\n(D) comprehensive live validation.\n\n## Context (current state)\n- **RC1 (fixed, #1):** reconciler CI used shallow `--depth=1` fetch + `git rebase`, resurrecting\n  compaction-deleted source files -> `SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT` (commit 5a7548a). Historical damage remains.\n- **RC2b (band A):** a concurrent write on a stale base gets an HLC below a peer's snapshot horizon; a\n  clean union-merge keeps it, but replay's positional skip drops it -> silent data loss.\n- **Invariant gap (band A):** docs I1 says compaction RENAMEs folded files to `*.retired`; the code hard-`os.remove()`s them.\n- **Convergence redesign (landed, epic file-lens-jewel; band B):** three-way-merge baseline + binding\n  lifecycle (ADRs 0026-0029, 0031) shipped, but the per-binding baseline runs dual-write SHADOW — the\n  Phase-3 consumer swap is not yet live, and two arbiters encode the rule twice.\n- **Latent reconciler gaps (band C):** silent same-field clobber with no conflict signal; hard-delete\n  -> re-create unreachable + false comment; silent field-allowlist drop; coarse bulk-path 429 handling.\n- **Validation gap (band D):** correctness is argued from code + an OSS/commercial comparison but not\n  PROVEN end-to-end against live Jira. Live validation is performed by an AGENT (ACLI access), with\n  guaranteed cleanup of test artifacts in both Jira and the local store — not deferred to the operator.\n- Design as a whole matches/beats OSS + commercial-tier peers. Single-hop status transitions are ACCEPTED / out of scope.\n\n## Success Criteria (target state)\n- **A. Store hardened + remediated:** compaction non-destructive (I1 `*.retired`); no concurrent\n  sub-horizon append silently dropped (RC2b); live-store `rebar fsck` reports zero\n  SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT / ORPHAN_EVENT / MISSING_CREATE.\n- **B. Convergence fully live:** the per-binding baseline is the authoritative direction arbiter\n  (Phase-3 consumer swap flipped + validated on live passes).\n- **C. Latent gaps closed:** true both-sides field conflicts recorded; hard-delete -> re-create works;\n  field-allowlist drops observable; bulk-path 429 honors Retry-After.\n- **D. Proven live:** the full bidirectional surface is validated against live Jira by an agent, with\n  GUARANTEED cleanup of every test artifact in both Jira and the local store.\n\n## Scope boundary\nThis epic is reconciler **correctness + validation**. Reconciler **maintainability/refactor** work —\noversized-function extraction (fusible-mean-porcupine), central git adapter (sewable-authorial-eagle),\nvendor-adapter seam (ambery-tweed-grosbeak), invariant detect/remediate split\n(inherited-genealogic-haddock), config split (seedy-edema-groan) — lives under the Janitor Cleanup\nepic, NOT here. Separate reconciler epics also stay separate: GitHub parity (slimy-tuber-stoop),\nauthenticated identity (gnu-whale-ichor), INDETERMINATE/LLM-gate handling (jira-reb-687).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Band A children landed: A1 (`*.retired`), A2 (RC2b horizon-safe; carries an approach decision), A3 (live-store remediation to zero fsck).\n- [ ] Band B: B1 (Phase-3 baseline consumer swap; agent performs its live validation with cleanup).\n- [ ] Band C children landed: C1 (clobber conflict signal), C2 (hard-delete re-create), C3 (field-allowlist alert), C4 (bulk-path 429 parity).\n- [ ] Band D: D1 (comprehensive live validation + guaranteed bilateral cleanup).\n- [ ] Dependency edges wired: A1->A2, A1->A3, A2->A3; C1 relates_to B1; D1 relates_to B1/C1/C2/C3/C4.\n- [ ] Risk #5 (single-hop status transitions) explicitly accepted / out of scope.\n\n\n## Cross-child coordination (verified in plan review)\n- SEQUENCING: A3's live remediation pauses the reconciler, which resets B1's >=10-consecutive-clean-shadow-pass\n  streak. Do NOT run A3's live pass during B1's streak window — sequence them.\n- SHARED FILE: C1 (feline-wandering-dassierat, `apply_outbound.py` conflict leaf ~207-232) and C3\n  (nonglacial-tense-vulture, `apply_outbound.py` ~117-124) edit the same file in different regions — coordinate merge order (relates_to linked).\n- VALIDATION ORDER: D1 (close-ferreous-cardinal) validates the POST-FIX behavior and runs AFTER the C-band lands;\n  captured in D1's body rather than as hard depends_on edges to avoid blocking-link promotion across mixed-type siblings.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783476734641029001,"uuid":"c913d160-b776-462a-a7d8-60322a5fdc28"}